canMap

public boolean canMap(DataMap map,
                      DataField local)
Checks is it is possible to map a local data element to a extrenal data element. The rule is that (1) the external data element and the local data element have to have the same DATA TYPE, and (2) it one local data element can be mapped only to one extrenal data element.

Parameters:
map - data mapping of a external data element
local - local data element
Returns:
true if the types of the external and local data elemets are the same and local dada element is not mapped to another external element.
